Product description

Colour Name:5M,1Pcs,Black&Red

HowiseAcc 16.5FT/5M Car Cigarette Lighter Socket Plug Extension Cable 

Extend the reach of your 12V/24V ports with this heavy duty extension cable.


What We Have Improved to Provide a Better User Experience?

Improved as 16.5ft extension cord, which help you extend the cigarette lighter socket to longer place.

Accurate size & premium quality male/female plug to make sure the stable connection.

Made of high quality copper wire with two insulating layers design, bult-in 15 Amp Fuse (6x30mm)  

Up to 4000 times bending performance, no more worry that the extension cable will be break and crack under flexure.


Specification:

Cable Length : 16.5feet / 5M

Input Voltage: DC 12V-24V 

Working Power: < 180W for 12V car, < 360W for 24V car 

Output Fuse: 15A


Guarantee:

12 months manufacturer warranty and superb customer service.

Question:
Would it be ok / possible / safe to connect 2 of these together to create a 10m extension?
Answer:
Absolutely, safety is not about the length more the current you wish to pull through it. The longer it gets the lower the current rating. If you are using something that only draws 2 amps then you could even put three together . Look at the wattage your item draws (if you don't know how many amp you are using) and div… see more Absolutely, safety is not about the length more the current you wish to pull through it. The longer it gets the lower the current rating. If you are using something that only draws 2 amps then you could even put three together . Look at the wattage your item draws (if you don't know how many amp you are using) and divide by 12 to give you current in amps (12v or 24 if 24v system) see less Absolutely, safety is not about the length more the current you wish to pull through it. The longer it gets the lower the current rating. If you are using something that only draws 2 amps then you could even put three together . Look at the wattage your item draws (if you don't know how many amp you are using) and divide by 12 to give you current in amps (12v or 24 if 24v system)

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.

1.0 out of 5 stars Completely useless item
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 11 August 2019
Colour Name: 5M,1Pcs,Black&RedVerified Purchase
It seems like this item has been previously returned by another customer who has tried to repair it. It is difficult to believe that the item was made as shown in the photo. Why would the manufacturer do that? So it seems that the returned item has been shipped out again without being checked. One wire in the socket had been disconnected or the joint had failed (looks like the former). The wires in the plug had been cut and then re-joined by twisting them together and stuffing the whole lot back into the plug. As a result, Positive and Negative wires were touching. Clearly someone has tried to use the item because the fuse had blown. This item has no redeeming features whatsoever and is completely useless. It is a piece of junk that deserves only to be in the bin. The merchant should be barred from future business for shipping an item in this condition. Absolutely zero quality control. I would score it zero stars if that were possible.
